title: Vegetable prices rise due to heavy rains and floods
byline: Agrarian Organisations in the Central Province warned that the already soaring prices of vegetables would further increase due to the prevailing heavy rain and floods, which have caused crop devastation.

title: Japan to consider new projects only after considering their economic status only: Embassy
byline: Japan will consider new projects in Sri Lanka only after examining any request from the Sri Lankan authorities and its economic status first, the Japanese Embassy said yesterday.

title: Neville Fernando Hospital to cater to health tourism
byline: The government is planning to develop Dr. Neville Fernando Teaching Hospital (NFTH) under a new model targeting health tourism, the Health Ministry said.

title: Lieutenant Commander killed in wild elephant attack
byline: A 41-year-old naval officer attached to the Punewa Navy camp was killed in a wild elephant attack last night, Police said.

title: Rainfall fuels rise in dengue and leptospirosis cases: Expert
byline: As a cyclonic storm sweeps over Sri Lanka, health experts warn of the spread of waterborne and communicable diseases in regions experiencing heavy rains and flooding.

title: Ceypetco revises fuel prices
byline: The Ceylon Petroleum Corporation (Ceypetco) has announced a revision of fuel prices, effective from midnight today.

title: Naval, fishing communities warned not to venture to sea till further notice
byline: Naval and fishing communities have been warned not to venture out to deep and shallow sea areas off the coast extending from Trincomalee to Puttalam via Kankesanthurai until further notice.

title: Government to take decision if Laugfs fails to supply gas: Minister
byline: The government will take a decision if Laugfs Gas fails to intervene to import and supply LP gas to the consumers, Minister of Trade, Commerce, Food Security and Cooperative Development Wasantha Samarasinghe said today.
